    {
      "id": "PopularPost263440",
      "post_content": "@Buderus: I absolutely love running modular creatures with Proliferate. I presume [Doubling Season](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doubling Season) as well, but even after all the times I've run my deck, I've yet to cast it and have modular creatures at hand. One day I will live the dream.  \n  \nI sincerely hope Wizards revisits modular, perhaps in a Planechase product or somewhere, so that I can replace the more lackluster creatures in my deck. While this guy's flavor text is great and his P/T isn't terrible (certainly not when he pumps up the evasive [Arcbound Fiend](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Fiend)), but there are certainly better designs they could print that would instantly replace (and [Arcbound Lancer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Lancer) and [Arcbound Wanderer](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Wanderer), if anyone runs those) this in modular decks everywhere.",
      "posted_by": "sarroth",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost263440\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_post\">@Buderus: I absolutely love running modular creatures with Proliferate. I presume <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Doubling Season\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Doubling Season\">Doubling Season</a> as well, but even after all the times I've run my deck, I've yet to cast it and have modular creatures at hand. One day I will live the dream.<br/><br/>I sincerely hope Wizards revisits modular, perhaps in a Planechase product or somewhere, so that I can replace the more lackluster creatures in my deck. While this guy's flavor text is great and his P/T isn't terrible (certainly not when he pumps up the evasive <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Fiend\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Fiend\">Arcbound Fiend</a>), but there are certainly better designs they could print that would instantly replace (and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Lancer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Lancer\">Arcbound Lancer</a> and <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Arcbound Wanderer\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Arcbound Wanderer\">Arcbound Wanderer</a>, if anyone runs those) this in modular decks everywhere.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl04_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '263440'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                    \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=\"postedBy\">\